    • Enum Constant Detail

      • ARGUMENT_LIST

        public static final BalanceType ARGUMENT_LIST
        No balance required, call arguments. 1) a = 5, b = 77 will be parsed as two arguments containing assignments

      • STATEMENT

        public static final BalanceType STATEMENT
        Zero balance required. Statement. Can be optimized keeping in mind that no results are expected. 1) a.b + 5 could be reduced to a.b cause it can produce side effects in form of error

      • DECLARATION

        public static final BalanceType DECLARATION
        Zero balance required. Declaration statement. var a = 5, b = 6, c = f(); portion between 'var ' and ';'

      • EXPRESSION

        public static final BalanceType EXPRESSION
        Object result required. Expression.

      • ARRAY_LITERAL

        public static final BalanceType ARRAY_LITERAL
        Array result required. 1) result is an array (instance of BaseNativeArray actually)
